cost_Q.Rd

Tidal Basin rainfall-runoff model as presented by Wan and Konyha (2015)

cost_Q(
  RF_2d,
  ETPI,
  RootStor = 1,
  Kc = 1,
  Z1.Smax = 1,
  Z1.StoreCef = 150,
  BasinArea = 251583,
  Z2.Smax = 1,
  Z2.StoreCef = 100,
  Z3.Smax = 2.2,
  Z3.StoreCef = 12,
  open.water.area = 0
)

Arguments

RF_2d

2-day moving average rainfall value for the Caloosahatchee Tidal Basin (current forecast models use SFWMD NEXRAD values)
ETPI

Regional evapotranspiration potential value for the (current forecast models use SFWMD DBKEY OH520)
RootStor

Capacity of root zone storage (i.e. maximum root zone storage). Default is 1 inch.
Kc

ET crop correction coefficient. Default is 1.
Z1.Smax

Capacity of subsurface (Zone 1) drainage storage. Default is 1 inch.
Z1.StoreCef

Storage coefficient of subsurface (Zone 1) drainage reservoir Default is 150.
BasinArea

Area of tidal basin. Caloosahatchee tidal basin area is 251,583 acres.
Z2.Smax

Capacity of surface (Zone 2) drainage storage. Default is 1 inch.
Z2.StoreCef

Storage coefficient of surface (Zone 2) drainage reservoir Default is 100.
Z3.Smax

Capacity of direct (Zone 3) drainage storage. Default is 2.2 inch.
Z3.StoreCef

Storage coefficient of direct (Zone 3) drainage reservoir Default is 12.
open.water.area

area of open water to estimate direct rainfall contribution.

Value

a vector of daily discharge values in cubic feet per second

References

Wan Y, Konyha K (2015) A simple hydrologic model for rapid prediction of runoff from ungauged coastal catchments. Journal of Hydrology 528:571–583. doi: 10.1016/j.jhydrol.2015.06.047
